#: ../../language/error_codes/E4042.md:1
msgid "E4042"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4042.md:3
msgid "Compiler diagnostic name: `invalid_stub_type`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4042.md:5
msgid "Invalid stub type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4042.md:7
msgid ""
"When defining an FFI function, each parameter and return type must be a "
"valid stub type that can be represented natively by the selected backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4042.md:10
msgid ""
"For example, `FixedArray[T]` is not a valid stub type for the Wasm GC "
"backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4042.md:12
msgid "Erroneous example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4042.md:14
msgid ""
"pub fn ffi(array : FixedArray[Int]) -> Unit = \"mod\" \"ffi\"\n"
"//                 ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\n"
"// Error: Invalid stub type.\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4042.md:18
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4042.md:20
msgid ""
"The way to pass non-native types through the FFI interface depends on "
"both the backend of the MoonBit compiler and the runtime you are using. "
"Use a native stub type directly, or pass a handle/index and manage the "
"compound value on the host side."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4042.md:25
msgid "pub fn ffi(value : Int) -> Unit = \"mod\" \"ffi\"\n"
msgstr ""
